This year’s top KCPE exam student studied at St Anne Junior School Lubao in Kakamega county. Parents, pupils and teachers yesterday gathered at the school in Webuye to celebrate Goldalyn Kakuya. Kakuya, 14, scored 455 marks.Her index number was 37616080001. She scored 99 per cent in English, 99 in Kiswahili, 85 in mathematics, 88 in science and 84 in social studies. “I’m honoured to be here today celebrating this victory. It’s wonderful because I only expected to do well, but not to be the top student in the country. I attribute this victory to God and hard work,” Kakuya said. Kakuya has albinism. Last year, the KCPE top candidate - Victor Oduor - scored 437 marks.          